headline: Qualcomm & McDonald's earnings, ADP job data: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch on Wednesday, Nov. 5. New York City's mayoral race is underway, with polls to close at 9:00 p.m. on Tuesday. Toyota (TM), Novo Nordisk (NVO), and McDonald's (MCD) will report quarterly earnings before the opening bell, while AppLovin (APP), Qualcomm (QCOM), and Robinhood (HOOD) report after the closing bell. ADP (ADP) will release employment data for October. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: McDonald's (NYSE:MCD) Reports Q3 In Line With Expectations

headline: McDonald’s U.S. Sales Rise. Why the Burger Giant’s Stock Is Slipping After Earnings.
summary: McDonald’s  failed to beat earnings and revenue forecasts in its third quarter, even as comparable sales rose from the previous year.  Adjusted earnings of $3.22 a share narrowly missed the $3.33 analysts had projected, according to FactSet.  Same-store sales increased 2.4% in the U.S. during the quarter, while global same-store sales rose 3.6%.

headline: Snack Wraps' return helps boost McDonald's third quarter sales
summary: McDonald’s sales got a lift from Snack Wraps in the third quarter.  Same-store sales rose 2.4% in the U.S. in the third quarter, the company said Wednesday.  U.S. traffic to McDonald’s stores was 15% higher than average on the day they were released, according to Placer.ai, a data company.
